HEADWORD: Symplectic
<hw>Sym*plec"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ plaiting
together, fr. <?/ to plait together.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Plaiting or joining together; -- said of a bone next above the
quadrate in the mandibular suspensorium of many fishes, which unites
together the other bones of the suspensorium.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The symplectic bone.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Symploce</ent>⟦br⟧
